{"id":"1908.04476","submitter":"Yantao Wu","authors":"Yantao Wu","title":"Dynamical Quantum Phase Transition of the Quantum $N$-state Potts Chain\n  with Quenched Disorder","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We present an exact renormalization group analysis of the Loschmidt amplitude\nof the quantum $N$-state Potts chain with random quench-disordered nearest\nneighbor bonds, under the extreme dynamical quantum quench. We prove that the\nphase transition of the Loschmidt rate function remains sharp in general. For\ntypical bond distributions, the phase transition is found to be a linear-cusp,\nas in the pure model. For some special discrete bond distributions, however,\nthe rate function exhibits logarithmic divergences. These singularities are due\nto the competition between the non-critical dynamical phases of the pure model,\nwhich is very different from how disorder affects equilibrium phase\ntransitions. In addition, due to the periodicity of the complex exponential\nfunction, all continuous bond distributions result in rate functions which\nconverge to a universal value at large time.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2019 03:47:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
